Subject: UTG - Account Maintenance

Team,

Here is a follow-up email for you regarding UTG and
Account Maintenance.

Currently, it will take an average of 6 minutes for an AM
to make a configuration change to one MID. These
configuration changes can range from anything as
simple as updating AVS settings to more involved
updates to the account that require a file build to be
performed. Below are some numbers showing how long

EX-10.4 3 ex10-4.htm AMENDMENT NO. 3 TO THE FIRST AMENDED AND RESTATED RESELLER AGREEMENT

it takes for an AM to perform the file builds.
Password Database SQR PCl File Other File
Builds Build Builds
20 Minutes 20 Minutes 35 Minutes 60 Minutes

The number of requests for updates has significantly
increased. In the past 6 months, we have averaged close
to 130 configuration changes per month (almost 30
per week). We also need to add around 80 new MIDs per
month.

As a result, the Account Maintenance team is facing
challenges keeping up with the workload. I had a
productive call with [Redacted] earlier today.
Below is a summary of our call. I think it would be
beneficial to start working towards a solution where
these configuration changes can be handled in UTG.

* [Redacted] and team are on board.
* This is a "big" project so at a minimum we are
looking at 3 months (potentially longer).
[Redacted]
*  [Redacted] recommended a phased approach to this by
first targeting a small set of the total configuration
options.
[Redacted] and his team could pull
the data on the most common configuration
changes to ensure we are targeting the correct
configuration options.
[Redacted] and I agreed that the first phase of
this project should allow UTG users to update AVS
settings.
* Payment Logistics currently handles these
changes in a portal offering.

-Daniel Halverson
